I voted YES to pass the #COVIDHateCrimesAct today. 

This bill improves hate crime reporting &amp; helps us better address bigotry against our neighbors, friends and loved ones.

@POTUS can now sign this into law!

Americans are still getting sick and dying. Many schools are still shuttered &amp; millions of workers are still struggling with or without unemployment help. 

Our nation needs the #AmericanRescuePlan. 

@HouseDemocrats delivered on our promise &amp; bring this lifeline #ForthePeople.

The American people are tired of the chaos, corruption &amp; inaction that has plagued our government. 

@HouseDemocrats are voting to put a stop to it. 

#HR1 delivers sweeping election &amp; anti-corruption reforms that will ensure a government of, by and for the people.

A once-in-a-century-crisis demands bold solutions.

The #AmericanRescuePlan lifts our nation to meet the needs of this moment. 

@HouseDemocrats are fighting to advance this lifeline to protect American lives &amp; get our economy back on track. I hope I can count on your support!

Now more than ever we must ensure our neighbors, friends and loved ones can get the mental health services they need.

@RepHuizenga and I introduced legislation to remove the Medicare 190 day inpatient treatment cap that private insurers ended long ago.

